{
  "stem": "27507.10",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The uprising in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The uprising, that's right.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The uprising was, of course, something that touched me very personally, because my father was still there.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My father was still in the ghetto, and some other family members.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And my father was in the Schultz shop, because Schultz ship, I think, was not itself completely destroyed yet during the uprising.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So what happened there to workers in the shop of Schultz, and to the workers in the shop of Toebbens, that's a digression, was that they were promised by the Germans that, although the ghetto is now destroyed and won't exist anymore, the workers are going to continue to work for the Wehrmacht, for the German army, except that they are going to be moved out of the ghetto and taken into a labor camp in Lublin area of Poland.",
      "word_count": 80
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And that was not like this time the Germans really took some people, management and so on, to show them that they mean business, that they really take those Jews to the labor camps, and not to any kind of destruction.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And it was all-- all done with many promises from the German management, and as well I think from the SS, probably that those workers have nothing to fear.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "As long as they work for the German army, they will survive the war.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So my father was in one of the last groups who remained in this factory.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And lots of those workers, and machines as well, that moved out of the ghetto into Trawniki, which was this labor camp in the Lublin area.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There were two such camps.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "One was Poniatowa, which was done for the workers of Toebbens, of another huge factory in ghetto.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And Trawniki was for Schultz.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
